script.name: Cmd.StationAgent
script.description: Cmd: Manages a station by buying or selling wares

line.comment: * Command status code:
* Standby: Waiting for station stock to increase
* Station Agent: Searching for a deal
* Idle: No stations found
* [THIS]-> connect ship command/signal [SIGNAL_ATTACKED] to script 'Sig.Attacked.StationAgent' with prio 100
* May as well refresh the ware times
* If inCargo is greater than zero at this point, it means that the ship couldnt
* unload because the station was full, but the ship has the ware to sell in cargo
* Mayhem: check if there's a station that wants the ware we want to sell.
* Basic synchronization with other station agents based on [HOMEBASE].
* We prioritize delivering to Sanctuaries before trading.
* $target = find station: sector=$homebaseSector class or type={*** UNDEFINED *** (SS_DOCK_SANCTUARY)} race=[Player] flags=0 refobj=null maxdist=0 maxnum=1 refpos=null
* gosub CheckError:
* Mayhem: check if there's a station that has the ware we need.
* Basic synchronization with other station agents based on [HOMEBASE].
* Not a percent!
* wait times for things like waiting for a station to produce
* a ware or a manager waiting for a ware to fall below 10 percent
* if $Code == -401
* [THIS]-> set orders string sprintf: fmt= 'Waiting, no stations will buy: %s' , $WareToSell , null , null , null , null
* else if $Code == -400
* [THIS]-> set orders string sprintf: fmt= 'Waiting, no stations will sell: %s' , $WareToBuy , null , null , null , null
* else
* end
* Checking to see if the station is paused.
* Ware
